  "text": "The Express.js repository contains three source files that specifically reference the deprecated req.host property. In lib/request.js (lines 454-456), the deprecated req.host property is defined using the depd deprecation module with the explicit deprecation message 'req.host: Use req.hostname instead'. This was introduced in Express 4.3.0 as noted in the History.md changelog (lines 1284-1286), which documents the addition of the newer req.hostname property as the correct replacement and explicitly lists the deprecation of req.host. The test/req.host.js file contains a comprehensive test suite for the req.host property, with multiple test cases covering basic functionality (lines 12, 25, 39), IPv6 support (lines 51, 64), and proxy trust settings (lines 80, 96, 112, 128, 145). The History.md changelog also includes additional historical notes about req.host functionality, such as fixes for IPv6 literals (line 1436) and X-Forwarded-Host support (line 2552), along with the original addition of req.host in Express 3.0.0 (line 2726)."
}

